  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A correlation between deep anesthesia (defined as time with Bispectral Index (BIS) lower than
      45) and death within 1 yr after surgery has previously been reported. In order to confirm or
      refute these findings, the investigators have designed a study which compares two methods of
      administration for total intravenous anesthesia (propofol and remifentanil):

        -  manual administration: the anesthesiologists are instructed to maintain the BIS value
           between 40 and 60.

        -  closed loop administration: an algorithm is used to maintain the BIS value between 40
           and 60.

      Based on previous studies, the amount of time that BIS is maintained above 40 is greater when
      anesthetics agents are administered using closed loop compared with manual administration.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
