  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  American Society of Anesthesiology patient classification status I, II and III

          -  patients aged between 50 and 85 years old

          -  born in France

          -  surgical procedures lasting more than one hour

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  American Society of Anesthesiology patient classification status IV

          -  patients born out of France

          -  pace-maker

          -  surgical procedure on the skull or avoiding an adequate positioning of the bispectral
             index electrode dementia, history of central nervous system disease (tumor, vascular
             event, Parkinson disease, ...)

          -  psychiatric illness (severe depression or psychosis), patients receiving a
             psychotropic treatment

          -  anesthesia performed during the year before inclusion in this study except for
             diagnostic procedures

          -  allergy to propofol, soja, peanuts, or to sufentanil, remifentanil, or morphine, to a
             myorelaxant or to an excipient,

          -  hypersensibility to sufentanil, to remifentanil, or to other derivate of fentanyl
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
    <gender>All</gender>
    <minimum_age>50 Years</minimum_age>
    <maximum_age>85 Years</maximum_age>
    <healthy_volunteers>No</healthy_volunteers>
